  "description": [
    "__ f 1 LITT LE MYRA i fKf Wi CUBA THE PARROT E bird and the baby arrived on the same day but Mary was far more interested in Cuba the parrot with her gay plumage than in the wee baby brother upstairs This was partly because Cuba was her very own sent by Uncle Leonard from the West Indies and the new baby was only a family possession Then too the bird was warranted to be a good talker and father said that little brother Would not be able to talk for a whole year So Mary spent all her time with Cuba and really gave very little thought to the baby Mary talked a steady stream as Thomas ealled it to her new pet yet days went by and the parrot could not be coaxed to say a word Mary became discouraged and feared that Uncle Leonard had been deceived in the bird At last one morning when she entered the living room Cuba looked up archly from the peanut she was eating and said Hello The one word seemed to unloose the little strangers tongue for after that she talked freely speaking of things in an almost"
